{"word":"G1573 - ἐκκακέω - ekkakéō - ek-kak-eh'-o - Faint","slug":"G1573","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἐκκακέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ekkakéō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ek-kak-eh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Faint"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>ἐκκακέω</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Ekkakeo</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>ek-kak-eh'-o</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> to be utterly spiritless, to be wearied out, exhausted </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G1537\">G1537</a> and <a href=\"#/G2556\">G2556</a> <p />- TDNT entry: TDNT 3:486,* <p />- Part(s) of speech: Verb <p />- Strong's: From <a href=\"#/G1537\">G1537</a> and <a href=\"#/G2556\">G2556</a>; to <i>be</i> (<i>bad</i> or) <i>weak</i> that is (by implication) to <i>fail</i> (in heart): - faint be weary. "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G172\">G172</a>, <a href=\"#/G2549\">G2549</a>, <a href=\"#/G2550\">G2550</a>, <a href=\"#/G2554\">G2554</a>, <a href=\"#/G2555\">G2555</a>, <a href=\"#/G2556\">G2556</a>, <a href=\"#/G2557\">G2557</a>, <a href=\"#/G420\">G420</a>"}]}